<br>
For offense, we need better itemization.  It never made much sense to me that since Pal/SK have lower cap they get weapons with way better ratio than anything warrior gets so that they end up doing comparable damage.  Warrior weapons tend to be inferior in ratio to everyone else's weapon which doesn't make much sense.  There needs to be more weapons like Acrylia Handled Broadsword that's good for everyone.  Fix taunt so we don't cripple ourselves on proc selection.  Also, make less mana guilt items.  If you must put Flowing Thought on all melee items then at least put some with negative mana to balance the fact that FT generally means automatic hybrid item.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thegiantone>TheGiantOne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/30/02 5:22:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Improve or not the warriors?</span><hr size=1> Read my last post under AA's or 65.  There are some valid concerns listed there.<br>
